Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.87,Base,,0,0,0,,Since we got here it's just been\N"basics, basics, basics"!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.87,0:00:08.80,Base,,0,0,0,,That's all we've done, every single class\Nsince we started here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.80,0:00:11.34,Base,,0,0,0,,And the Phantom's class is the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:13.84,Base,,0,0,0,,We could ask for something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:15.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Let's ask Andou-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.24,0:00:37.49,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Everyone dreams of becoming a superstar at least once
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.49,0:00:42.77,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}So that you can make the world envious
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.77,0:00:45.52,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}1, 2, 3, quick like Allegro
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:47.79,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Hold that hand and come
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.79,0:00:52.34,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Let's build a rainbow together at Andante
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:58.60,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}You aren't anyone yet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.60,0:01:03.71,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}So any of your future can come true
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:09.72,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Your dream is just beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.21,0:01:14.39,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Little by little, you can become yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:20.31,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Tomorrow's gonna blow another wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.31,0:01:24.23,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}So dream as many times as you want
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.23,0:01:29.71,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}Someday, become the stage's sparkling star
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.71,0:01:34.92,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}{\blur9}so that the spotlight shines upon you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:47.48,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"A Glimpse of Stardom"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:50.44,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"A Glimpse of Stardom"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:50.44,Base,,0,0,0,,Today, we'll be talking about the\NStanislavski technique and how to--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.44,0:01:54.11,Base,,0,0,0,,Today, we'll be talking about the\NStanislavski technique and how to--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.11,0:01:58.99,Base,,0,0,0,,Why do you all look dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.99,0:02:02.20,Base,,0,0,0,,Andou-sensei! Can I make a suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:03.12,Base,,0,0,0,,She's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.12,0:02:05.29,Base,,0,0,0,,She's actually asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:08.25,Base,,0,0,0,,What are you girls plotting?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.25,0:02:09.92,Base,,0,0,0,,Shoot, Watanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:10.96,Base,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:16.96,Base,,0,0,0,,So, there's one crucial skill that\Nevery other teacher has mentioned to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.96,0:02:18.55,Base,,0,0,0,,Expression!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.55,0:02:21.09,Base,,0,0,0,,Expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:23.81,Base,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Expression!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.81,0:02:28.23,Base,,0,0,0,,I knew who every teacher was\Nwithout her even saying their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:29.06,Base,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.06,0:02:32.44,Base,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And {\i0}I believe the one class\Nwhere we'll learn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.44,0:02:35.57,Base,,0,0,0,,{\i1}how {\i0}to express ourselves is this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:37.74,Base,,0,0,0,,We've been Kouka students for four months,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:41.53,Base,,0,0,0,,so we think it might be nice if we, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:45.20,Base,,0,0,0,,had a little opportunity to actually {\i1}act{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.75,0:02:51.92,Base,,0,0,0,,Is that your suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:02:58.42,Base,,0,0,0,,Well, I've been here eight years, and the\Nfirst-year's curriculum has never changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:02.89,Base,,0,0,0,,First-year students are expected to sit\Npolitely and learn the basics of acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.89,0:03:06.47,Base,,0,0,0,,That's how it's been done at\Nthe Kouka School for a century now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:10.60,Base,,0,0,0,,But here's an idea, Watanabe!\NDo that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:11.56,Base,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.56,0:03:14.94,Base,,0,0,0,,Show me what I sound like\Nwhen I say "expression."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:17.94,Base,,0,0,0,,If I think it's good,\NI'll consider your suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:21.65,Base,,0,0,0,,Those are high stakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.65,0:03:25.28,Base,,0,0,0,,Got a lot of pressure on me,\Nbut here goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:30.79,Base,,0,0,0,,Expression? What's that,\Nsome hot new band?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.00,0:03:36.34,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, open your textbooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:37.63,Base,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:39.84,Base,,0,0,0,,So much for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:42.55,Base,,0,0,0,,Sorry I couldn't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:43.84,Base,,0,0,0,,Actually, Sara--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.84,0:03:48.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Watanabe-san, that was a good\Nimpression of Andou-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.39,0:03:49.60,Base,,0,0,0,,It so was!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:52.52,Base,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was {\i1}too {\i0}good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:56.65,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, Watanabe-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:59.53,Base,,0,0,0,,There's a package here for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:05.78,Base,,0,0,0,,13, 14, 15, 16 roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.78,0:04:08.53,Base,,0,0,0,,Sara-- Watanabe-san, is today...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.53,0:04:12.08,Base,,0,0,0,,Yep! I turn 16 years old today!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.08,0:04:13.33,Base,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.33,0:04:15.04,Base,,0,0,0,,Today's your birthday?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:17.09,Base,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:18.71,Base,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.71,0:04:21.59,Base,,0,0,0,,Aww, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:25.18,Base,,0,0,0,,My first friend's birthday is today...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.18,0:04:28.72,Base,,0,0,0,,So who gave you this bouquet of roses?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:30.43,Base,,0,0,0,,Is it a guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.43,0:04:32.10,Base,,0,0,0,,Ohmigosh, your boyfriend?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.10,0:04:35.98,Base,,0,0,0,,Maybe! He lives in Tokyo,\Nso we're long-distance right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.98,0:04:38.02,Base,,0,0,0,,but it could be him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.36,0:04:42.32,Base,,0,0,0,,A-And he's a real, live person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.32,0:04:43.82,Base,,0,0,0,,Not some anime guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.82,0:04:48.53,Base,,0,0,0,,Is that the person\Nyou're always messaging?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.87,0:04:52.08,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Happy Birthday"\N"from your fan of the red rose"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:55.33,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Happy Birthday"\N"from your fan of the red rose"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:55.33,Base,,0,0,0,,What the hell? That's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.33,0:05:00.13,Base,,0,0,0,,Sara-- Watanabe-san, does your boyfriend\Nlike these sorts of gestures?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.13,0:05:02.63,Base,,0,0,0,,That's hard to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.13,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Kouzaburou"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:07.80,Base,,0,0,0,,You sure are in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.80,0:05:13.64,Base,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't I be?\NIt's my darling Sarasa's 16th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.64,0:05:16.06,Base,,0,0,0,,You knew that, right, Akiya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:17.40,Base,,0,0,0,,Of course I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:23.07,Base,,0,0,0,,So, did you send her a present?\NYou {\i1}are {\i0}her boyfriend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:27.66,Base,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna give it to her\Nwhen she comes home this summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:34.00,Base,,0,0,0,,C'mon, where's your passion?\NI sent her a bouquet of 16 roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.00,0:05:37.29,Base,,0,0,0,,She's so incredibly special to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.29,0:05:40.00,Base,,0,0,0,,And this is her special day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:41.67,Base,,0,0,0,,Wait... hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.67,0:05:46.13,Base,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I didn't say it was from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:47.22,Base,,0,0,0,,I said it was from\Nher "fan of the red rose."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:49.89,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Happy Birthday"\N"from your fan of the red rose"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:49.89,Base,,0,0,0,,I said it was from\Nher "fan of the red rose."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:52.26,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Happy Birthday"\N"from your fan of the red rose"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.89,0:05:52.26,Base,,0,0,0,,Her fan of the red rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:05:57.44,Base,,0,0,0,,Forget summer vacation. Why not just\Nsend her something now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:06:01.27,Base,,0,0,0,,I'll send her a text message tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.27,0:06:04.53,Base,,0,0,0,,You gonna stop by her grandpa's\Nplace tonight again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:06.61,Base,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.49,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Happy Birthday, Sarasa-chan! I'll give you\Nyour present over summer break!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:17.08,Base,,0,0,0,,Her boyfriend's a frog? And a bot at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:19.37,Base,,0,0,0,,But why does a bot have a private account?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:24.55,Base,,0,0,0,,I won't let that frog outdo me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:28.72,Base,,0,0,0,,I wanna give Watanabe-san something\Nshe'll love even more than those roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:32.26,Base,,0,0,0,,After all, she's the first\Nfriend I ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.26,0:06:37.14,Base,,0,0,0,,And now's the perfect chance\Nto call her by her first name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.14,0:06:39.60,Base,,0,0,0,,Should I add -chan because\Nshe's younger than me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.60,0:06:42.61,Base,,0,0,0,,Sarasa-tan? Saracchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:45.40,Base,,0,0,0,,Or do I keep it simple with Sarasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.36,0:06:47.40,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.65,0:06:51.20,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.20,0:06:57.66,Base,,0,0,0,,The hardest-to-get lottery prize figurine\Nof Tsukahara Vault Taku!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.66,0:07:00.71,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, Taku-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.79,0:07:06.09,Base,,0,0,0,,Ai-chan, you got this for me,\Ndidn't you?! I could cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.09,0:07:09.76,Base,,0,0,0,,I tried four times to win it\Nand only won hand towels!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:11.01,Base,,0,0,0,,Well, Sara--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:14.47,Base,,0,0,0,,Watanabe-san, you're always\Ngoing on and on about {\i1}Floor Kings{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.47,0:07:17.43,Base,,0,0,0,,so I gave it a go and won the top prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.43,0:07:19.14,Base,,0,0,0,,In one try?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.14,0:07:21.44,Base,,0,0,0,,No, after a half-dozen tries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:22.35,Base,,0,0,0,,You like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.35,0:07:24.48,Base,,0,0,0,,I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.48,0:07:26.02,Base,,0,0,0,,Especially this part!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:29.03,Base,,0,0,0,,"To Sarasa. Sorry it's late.\NHappy birthday."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:30.45,Base,,0,0,0,,Don't read it out loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.45,0:07:32.74,Base,,0,0,0,,But look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:34.28,Base,,0,0,0,,"To Sarasa"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.28,0:07:37.79,Base,,0,0,0,,Look, Sa... Watanabe-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:43.12,Base,,0,0,0,,Just call me Sarasa!\NWe're friends, aren't we, Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:47.75,Base,,0,0,0,,Sarasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:54.01,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, Taku-sama! Ai-chan called me "Sarasa"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.01,0:07:55.97,Base,,0,0,0,,I can die happy now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.93,0:07:58.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.51,0:08:01.27,Base,,0,0,0,,I had a meeting with\Nthe other teachers yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.27,0:08:04.77,Base,,0,0,0,,and they said we could\Nchange up the curriculum.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.77,0:08:06.27,Base,,0,0,0,,Quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:09.61,Base,,0,0,0,,We're going to perform a scene from\NShakespeare's {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.61,0:08:12.45,Base,,0,0,0,,The roles are Romeo, Juliet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.45,0:08:17.41,Base,,0,0,0,,Tybalt, and Juliet's Nurse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.41,0:08:21.29,Base,,0,0,0,,Each group of four will have two weeks\Nto prepare their scene on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.29,0:08:22.12,Base,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:23.25,Base,,0,0,0,,On our own?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:26.54,Base,,0,0,0,,Andou-sensei, what do you mean\Nby "on our own"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:27.92,Base,,0,0,0,,Is this not a class activity?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.92,0:08:29.46,Base,,0,0,0,,We got duped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:30.96,Base,,0,0,0,,Some teacher he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.96,0:08:36.30,Base,,0,0,0,,Now, now, I {\i1}did {\i0}have to fight a bit\Nin that faculty meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:40.68,Base,,0,0,0,,They let us do this under the assumption\Nthat this would be an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:45.40,Base,,0,0,0,,So I haven't prepared any materials\Nor plans for guiding you to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.40,0:08:48.69,Base,,0,0,0,,You'll rehearse on your own,\Nthen in two weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.69,0:08:53.32,Base,,0,0,0,,we'll spend one class period\Npresenting our scenes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:56.91,Base,,0,0,0,,and I'll give you {\i1}thorough{\i0}\Nfeedback on your performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.28,0:09:01.16,Base,,0,0,0,,Also, since this was your idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:05.00,Base,,0,0,0,,you won't complain if we end up\Nusing it for next year's class, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:06.50,Base,,0,0,0,,Crafty bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:08.63,Base,,0,0,0,,Of course, we don't have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.63,0:09:10.21,Base,,0,0,0,,We'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:15.97,Base,,0,0,0,,We drew lots to determine\Nwho'd be in each of the five groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:17.01,Base,,0,0,0,,Group E.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.18,0:09:19.85,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Group E"\N"Sarasa Watanabe"\N"Hoshino Kaoru"\N"Chika Sawada"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.85,0:09:21.47,Base,,0,0,0,,Guess we're with you, Sarasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:24.77,Base,,0,0,0,,Yep! Let's break a leg, Group E!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:26.73,Base,,0,0,0,,How do we wanna pick roles?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:31.48,Base,,0,0,0,,Sarasa and I both want to be {\i1}otoko-yaku{\i0},\Nso we'll pick between Romeo and Tybalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:32.78,Base,,0,0,0,,Rock-paper-scissors?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.78,0:09:33.65,Base,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:37.07,Base,,0,0,0,,Then Naracchi and I will play\Nthe {\i1}musume-yaku {\i0}parts!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.07,0:09:38.74,Base,,0,0,0,,Want to do rock-paper-scissors, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:39.57,Base,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.57,0:09:41.08,Base,,0,0,0,,Rock, paper, scissors!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:43.79,Base,,0,0,0,,Sweet! I'll take Romeo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.79,0:09:46.37,Base,,0,0,0,,That means I'm Tybalt!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:47.29,Base,,0,0,0,,What about you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:50.29,Base,,0,0,0,,Rock, paper, scissors!\NRock, paper, scissors!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.92,0:09:58.63,Base,,0,0,0,,Um, I'll play, uh, Ju...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.63,0:09:59.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Juliet's Nurse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:00.34,Base,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.34,0:10:05.77,Base,,0,0,0,,I mean, I wanted to play that! A comic\Nrole will be the perfect challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.77,0:10:07.89,Base,,0,0,0,,You'll make a better Juliet\Nthan me, anyway, Naracchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.89,0:10:11.44,Base,,0,0,0,,Really? I can play Juliet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:13.11,Base,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.11,0:10:15.49,Base,,0,0,0,,--I've always {\i1}loved {\i0}the Kouka version\Nof Juliet! I'm so happy right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.49,0:10:17.07,Base,,0,0,0,,--Oh, it's fine.\N--I've always {\i1}loved {\i0}the Kouka version\Nof Juliet! I'm so happy right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.07,0:10:19.49,Base,,0,0,0,,I wanted to play the Nurse, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.49,0:10:22.24,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay. Then Naracchi's our Juliet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:23.28,Base,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.95,0:10:28.33,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Tatami Room"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.71,0:10:30.75,Base,,0,0,0,,Let's start with a quick readthrough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:34.50,Base,,0,0,0,,To be honest, I think Sarasa\Nwould be better off as Romeo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:36.59,Base,,0,0,0,,instead of the darker Tybalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.76,0:10:41.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Especially after that evening when\Nwe were walking back from the theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.39,0:10:46.52,Base,,0,0,0,,and she recited those few\Nperfect lines as Romeo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:48.18,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, you start, Chika.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.18,0:10:49.81,Base,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:56.44,Base,,0,0,0,,Madam, your mother craves a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.44,0:10:59.28,Base,,0,0,0,,Good woman! Who is her mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:04.58,Base,,0,0,0,,Why sir, her mother is the lady\Nof the house, Lady Capulet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:08.08,Base,,0,0,0,,A Capulet?! O dear account!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:09.00,Base,,0,0,0,,She's up next.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:12.71,Base,,0,0,0,,Show me the passion that's\Ndriving you to become a top star.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.71,0:11:14.67,Base,,0,0,0,,Show us all you've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:20.22,Base,,0,0,0,,That voice, is that Romeo?\NRomeo, of house Montague?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:27.93,Base,,0,0,0,,How dare the man come hither,\Nto the Cap... Capulet? Mansion itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.93,0:11:29.23,Base,,0,0,0,,How are you this bad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:30.77,Base,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:33.23,Base,,0,0,0,,Stop messing around and get serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.23,0:11:36.11,Base,,0,0,0,,I-I wasn't messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.11,0:11:38.32,Base,,0,0,0,,Whatever! We don't have time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.32,0:11:40.19,Base,,0,0,0,,Juliet, your lines are next!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:51.00,Base,,0,0,0,,See?! Your crappy reading\Nthrew Naracchi off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.00,0:11:55.00,Base,,0,0,0,,My, what are you all doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:56.54,Base,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.54,0:11:59.13,Base,,0,0,0,,What's this about? Some secret meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.13,0:12:03.97,Base,,0,0,0,,Just kidding! Andou-sensei filled us\Nall in on your little scene exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:09.56,Base,,0,0,0,,You first-years are already getting\Nto act? Boy, you girls are lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.56,0:12:13.52,Base,,0,0,0,,And you're doing {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0}?\NI love that show!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.52,0:12:18.11,Base,,0,0,0,,One thing, though: you really can't\Nuse this room to practice, mmkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:19.57,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"First-Year Lockers"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:20.74,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"First-Year Lockers"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:20.74,Base,,0,0,0,,Hijiri-senpai was really mad at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.74,0:12:22.40,Base,,0,0,0,,Hijiri-senpai was really mad at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:24.74,Base,,0,0,0,,She was? But she was all smiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:28.37,Base,,0,0,0,,That's how you can tell when\Nshe's angry--she's {\i1}smiling{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:30.75,Base,,0,0,0,,Ugh, we can't use the tatami room anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:33.46,Base,,0,0,0,,Where should we practice\Nfrom now on, then, Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.46,0:12:38.88,Base,,0,0,0,,Group A's using the lecture hall,\Nbut they might let us share it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:42.34,Base,,0,0,0,,Hey, can we use half\Nthe lecture hall with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:43.30,Base,,0,0,0,,I don't see why not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.30,0:12:44.84,Base,,0,0,0,,--Sure.\N--Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.84,0:12:46.18,Base,,0,0,0,,W-We can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.18,0:12:47.35,Base,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.35,0:12:51.72,Base,,0,0,0,,W-We're doing the same scene,\Nso we'll throw each other off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:55.27,Base,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna share a place\Nto practice with another group!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:13:00.32,Base,,0,0,0,,Then where do we practice?\NAll the other rooms are already taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:03.07,Base,,0,0,0,,Why don't we just do it\Nout on the sidewalk?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.07,0:13:04.03,Base,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:06.78,Base,,0,0,0,,The sidewalk?! Are you insane?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.78,0:13:11.49,Base,,0,0,0,,We are students of the 100th class\Nof the {\i1}esteemed {\i0}Kouka School!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:16.62,Base,,0,0,0,,We can't perform on the sidewalk!\NWhat a way to ruin Kouka for everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:20.92,Base,,0,0,0,,We might be students now, but we are\Ndestined to be professionals!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.92,0:13:23.21,Base,,0,0,0,,You'd better drill that\Ninto your skull, got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.18,0:13:29.01,Base,,0,0,0,,I have to use the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.26,0:13:32.77,Base,,0,0,0,,That scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.77,0:13:36.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Who pissed her off? You {\i1}know{\i0}\Nshe's got a really short fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:38.10,Base,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:43.48,Base,,0,0,0,,Her mom was a Kouka actress,\Nand her grandma was a top {\i1}musume-yaku{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.48,0:13:46.07,Base,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine the kind of pressure\Nthat puts on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.66,0:13:49.07,Base,,0,0,0,,Hoshino-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:56.50,Base,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know. I'm a loudmouth\Nwith a short fuse, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.50,0:14:00.33,Base,,0,0,0,,There was a girl like you in JPX.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.33,0:14:02.84,Base,,0,0,0,,She was our group leader\Nand was always angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.84,0:14:07.01,Base,,0,0,0,,What, you come to rub it in?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.01,0:14:11.72,Base,,0,0,0,,I never went to high school, and barely\Nwent to elementary and middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:17.73,Base,,0,0,0,,So Sarasa wasn't the reason I couldn't\Nread Juliet's lines this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.73,0:14:19.10,Base,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.10,0:14:21.73,Base,,0,0,0,,...can't read kanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:23.19,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Favorite Place: beech"\N"Why: Its suthing"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:29.24,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Favorite Place: beech"\N"Why: Its suthing"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:29.24,Base,,0,0,0,,Back in JPX, I was used to my manager\Nwriting the readings down for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:33.83,Base,,0,0,0,,This morning was the first time\NI realized how screwed I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:36.33,Base,,0,0,0,,None of us have any experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.33,0:14:40.67,Base,,0,0,0,,so unless you get mad at us,\Nwe'll just end up holding you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.67,0:14:43.46,Base,,0,0,0,,What the hell? That's so not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.46,0:14:46.67,Base,,0,0,0,,What if I don't want to be\Nthe bad guy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.97,0:14:50.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Then Group E fails together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.51,0:14:52.18,Base,,0,0,0,,Is that a threat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.47,0:14:54.35,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Nono Park"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:54.93,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Nono Park"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:54.93,Base,,0,0,0,,Ta-dah! Well? Isn't it perfect?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.93,0:14:57.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Ta-dah! Well? Isn't it perfect?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.39,0:14:59.44,Base,,0,0,0,,It's not the sidewalk, that's for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:02.98,Base,,0,0,0,,Chika-chan and I looked all over\Nfor a good spot to practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:05.07,Base,,0,0,0,,Will this work, Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:07.15,Base,,0,0,0,,Not like we can go anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.15,0:15:12.95,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, we've got two weeks to prep this\Nscene that's not gonna teach us anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.95,0:15:14.24,Base,,0,0,0,,C'mon, Group E!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:15.95,Base,,0,0,0,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.95,0:15:18.29,Base,,0,0,0,,Really, Sugimoto-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:21.67,Base,,0,0,0,,You're gonna lend me your Blu-ray of\NWinter Troupe {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.67,0:15:23.58,Base,,0,0,0,,Kaoru asked me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.58,0:15:26.63,Base,,0,0,0,,She said if you don't level up, and fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.63,0:15:30.30,Base,,0,0,0,,then "Group E's gonna drag\Nthe rest of our class down with them."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:34.26,Base,,0,0,0,,That Hoshino-san doesn't mince words, huh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.26,0:15:35.93,Base,,0,0,0,,Ai-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:40.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Sugimoto-san lent me her copy\Nof {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0}! Wanna watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:44.23,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Kanji Dictionary"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:44.23,Base,,0,0,0,,I'm good. I gotta spend all night\Nwriting kanji readings onto our script.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:48.74,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay! Could I borrow your\NBlu-ray player and headphones?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.74,0:15:50.45,Base,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:54.78,Base,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna study so hard, I'm gonna\Nknock the socks off Hoshino-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:55.78,Base,,0,0,0,,Mmkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.78,0:15:58.24,Base,,0,0,0,,Let's do an awesome job tomorrow morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:15:59.29,Base,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.50,0:16:05.38,Base,,0,0,0,,I wonder where the Sarasa\NI saw that day disappeared to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.29,0:16:08.50,Base,,0,0,0,,That voice, is that Romeo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.50,0:16:11.42,Base,,0,0,0,,Romeo, of house Montague?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.42,0:16:16.64,Base,,0,0,0,,How dare the man come hither,\Nto the Capulet mansion itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.64,0:16:19.10,Base,,0,0,0,,Such sins shall not be endured!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.10,0:16:21.89,Base,,0,0,0,,Such sins shall not be endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:27.48,Base,,0,0,0,,So, how's your Group E looking, Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.48,0:16:29.03,Base,,0,0,0,,And by that, I mean, how's Sarasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.03,0:16:31.57,Base,,0,0,0,,I kinda don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:33.28,Base,,0,0,0,,Like, it's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:34.78,Base,,0,0,0,,Creepy how?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.78,0:16:38.45,Base,,0,0,0,,You know how you're supposed to\Nimprove little by little?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.45,0:16:40.87,Base,,0,0,0,,Sarasa just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:48.63,Base,,0,0,0,,I'm so nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.63,0:16:53.42,Base,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Andou-sensei doesn't\Nexpect us to be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.42,0:16:57.60,Base,,0,0,0,,Then why did the Phantom\Neven want us to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.60,0:17:00.35,Base,,0,0,0,,Probably because he wanted\Nto see how much fun we'd have,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:03.64,Base,,0,0,0,,or how much effort we'd put into it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:04.89,Base,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:09.02,Base,,0,0,0,,I mean, isn't playing pretend\Nway more fun when you've got friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:11.78,Base,,0,0,0,,We only had two weeks\Nto put this together,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.78,0:17:14.11,Base,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure that even when I\Nfinally get to play Lady Oscar,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.11,0:17:18.62,Base,,0,0,0,,I'll remember these last two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:21.87,Base,,0,0,0,,Enough about Oscar. That {\i1}was {\i0}fun, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:23.41,Base,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter if we mess up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.41,0:17:26.67,Base,,0,0,0,,Just keep going until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.67,0:17:29.34,Base,,0,0,0,,But give it your all, okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.34,0:17:32.55,Base,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We'll give it 100% to the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.55,0:17:34.92,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, each group gets\N15 minutes to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:39.01,Base,,0,0,0,,I've marked out the 'stage' with tape,\Nso use that as a guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.01,0:17:40.47,Base,,0,0,0,,Group A is first...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.47,0:17:44.43,Base,,0,0,0,,...most of the time,\Nso let's go with Group E.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.43,0:17:46.69,Base,,0,0,0,,We have to go {\i1}first{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:49.90,Base,,0,0,0,,We didn't even think about\Nthe size of the actual stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:53.03,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's imagine it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.03,0:17:55.65,Base,,0,0,0,,There's a balcony up above,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.65,0:17:57.91,Base,,0,0,0,,and a big ballroom in the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.91,0:17:59.99,Base,,0,0,0,,The lights are tinged with blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.99,0:18:03.29,Base,,0,0,0,,and there's a crescent moon\Nthrough the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.29,0:18:05.37,Base,,0,0,0,,What beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.37,0:18:10.79,Base,,0,0,0,,She shines like\Na rich jewel amidst the crowd!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.79,0:18:13.92,Base,,0,0,0,,Love! This, truly, is love!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:16.88,Base,,0,0,0,,--My life's road has led me\Nto her beautiful flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:17.84,Base,,0,0,0,,--C'mon, now.\N--My life's road has led me\Nto her beautiful flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:20.39,Base,,0,0,0,,Stop trying to gauge my reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:23.31,Base,,0,0,0,,Keep looking at me,\Nand you'll flub your lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:26.10,Base,,0,0,0,,Good woman! Who is her mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:29.73,Base,,0,0,0,,--Why sir, her mother is the\Nlady of the house, Lady Capulet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.73,0:18:32.11,Base,,0,0,0,,--She sure is spry for an old lady.\N--Why sir, her mother is the\Nlady of the house, Lady Capulet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.11,0:18:36.03,Base,,0,0,0,,Her daughter is a visage of beauty,\Nand intelligent, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.03,0:18:39.16,Base,,0,0,0,,How fortunate I am to have nursed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.16,0:18:42.95,Base,,0,0,0,,She is a visage of beauty, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.95,0:18:44.41,Base,,0,0,0,,I messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.75,0:18:50.00,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I'm gonna cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.00,0:18:51.54,Base,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter if we mess up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:55.59,Base,,0,0,0,,Just keep going until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:56.80,Base,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:19:00.26,Base,,0,0,0,,I felt those qualities of such importance,\NI said them twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:03.18,Base,,0,0,0,,Nice save.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.18,0:19:06.89,Base,,0,0,0,,My! Come hither, nurse!\NWhere goeth yonder gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:09.56,Base,,0,0,0,,The man with visage radiant as the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.56,0:19:14.07,Base,,0,0,0,,I can tell she's had experience\Nbeing on a big stage before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:16.73,Base,,0,0,0,,--There, him now who is going out of door!\N--But boy, this Juliet...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.73,0:19:19.32,Base,,0,0,0,,...is {\i1}so {\i0}not in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.32,0:19:23.70,Base,,0,0,0,,--Go ask his name, if he be married...\N--Still, she keeps looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.70,0:19:26.45,Base,,0,0,0,,And not how Hoshino was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:28.25,Base,,0,0,0,,--My only love, sprung from my only hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:30.54,Base,,0,0,0,,--Hold on, Narata...\N--My only love, sprung from my only hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:33.71,Base,,0,0,0,,Are you performing for\Nan audience of {\i1}one{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:35.75,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, next up, our Kouka misfit,\NSarasa Watanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.75,0:19:37.76,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Group E Roles"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.75,0:19:37.76,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay, next up, our Kouka misfit,\NSarasa Watanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:42.14,Base,,0,0,0,,That voice, is that Romeo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:44.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Romeo, of house Montague?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.51,0:19:49.93,Base,,0,0,0,,How dare the man come hither,\Nto the Capulet mansion itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.93,0:19:52.06,Base,,0,0,0,,She's directing her gaze\Nat the balcony seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.06,0:19:55.19,Base,,0,0,0,,And she's keeping her eyes at a 45-degree\Nangle so the lights will catch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.19,0:19:56.32,Base,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.32,0:19:59.90,Base,,0,0,0,,Fetch me my rapier, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.20,0:20:02.82,Base,,0,0,0,,That Romeo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:05.53,Base,,0,0,0,,...is naught but a villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.49,0:20:11.75,Base,,0,0,0,,Sarasa Watanabe was reborn overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.75,0:20:15.59,Base,,0,0,0,,And because today, she has an audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.59,0:20:17.00,Base,,0,0,0,,it's even more--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:20.63,Base,,0,0,0,,Okay! Good job, Group E.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:24.97,Base,,0,0,0,,Here's a question for you.\NWho did you imagine as your audience?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:26.60,Base,,0,0,0,,The people in this room right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:29.31,Base,,0,0,0,,I-I didn't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.31,0:20:31.56,Base,,0,0,0,,A full house with balcony seats!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.56,0:20:32.85,Base,,0,0,0,,One person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:35.73,Base,,0,0,0,,So that's why you were\Nstaring at me that whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:36.61,Base,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:40.49,Base,,0,0,0,,In JPX, they told us that even if\Nwe only had an audience of one,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.49,0:20:45.20,Base,,0,0,0,,we should direct our performance\Ntowards them and give it our all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:47.33,Base,,0,0,0,,That's a good thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.33,0:20:53.75,Base,,0,0,0,,but the Kouka theater holds 2,500 people,\Nand every performance is a full house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:58.50,Base,,0,0,0,,When you're acting, you should act\Nfor every one of those 2,500 people!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.50,0:20:59.59,Base,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.59,0:21:03.47,Base,,0,0,0,,Also, Narata, if you're going to play\Na {\i1}musume-yaku{\i0}, try to be a little sweeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.47,0:21:06.84,Base,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I've seen\Na Juliet who didn't smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.84,0:21:08.26,Base,,0,0,0,,Next, Chika Sawada!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:09.51,Base,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.51,0:21:13.56,Base,,0,0,0,,Great recovery after\Nyou flubbed your line there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.56,0:21:17.44,Base,,0,0,0,,But hunching over doesn't\Nmake you an old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:19.40,Base,,0,0,0,,Use that imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.40,0:21:20.86,Base,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.86,0:21:21.90,Base,,0,0,0,,Next up, Hoshino.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.90,0:21:22.74,Base,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:25.61,Base,,0,0,0,,Don't let your mind stray\Nwhen you're performing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.61,0:21:27.57,Base,,0,0,0,,Leave yourself behind\Nwhen you step on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.57,0:21:30.66,Base,,0,0,0,,--Okay, next!\N--Wait, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.66,0:21:32.75,Base,,0,0,0,,For now, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.75,0:21:35.33,Base,,0,0,0,,You haven't learned any skills yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.33,0:21:39.17,Base,,0,0,0,,so I want you to act\Nhowever you want for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.17,0:21:43.17,Base,,0,0,0,,Don't get too hung up on my critique.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.17,0:21:44.72,Base,,0,0,0,,Right, last up, Watanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:46.22,Base,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:48.89,Base,,0,0,0,,Your impression was uncanny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.89,0:21:51.68,Base,,0,0,0,,I'll admit, I was shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:54.10,Base,,0,0,0,,But I'm sorry, Watanabe,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:57.10,Base,,0,0,0,,you'll never be a top star.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.02,0:22:04.57,Base,,0,0,0,,If you don't change, you'll never be\Na top star of the Kouka Revue.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:39.91,Base,,0,0,0,,{\an8}"Act 7: The Hanamichi\Nand the Silver Bridge"
